</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>HR64:v99#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="HR64"/><meta name="dc:title" content="HR &#xA;              64-&#xA;                INTRODUCED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td align="center"/></tr></tbody></table></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><font size="3" style="FONT-FAMILY: MinionPC, Arial Unicode MS">
                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                House Resolution
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 64</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Assembly Member Hoover<br/></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>August 27, 2025</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> Relative to World Meditation Day. </span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">HR 64, as introduced, Hoover.
                          </span></div><div><span id="digesttext"/></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_B440EAE3-CFBF-4DFE-B035-E962FCA7E945"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, For many years, meditation teachers and students desired a collective global celebration of the over 5,000-year-old mental and spiritual practice of meditation, including meditation teacher Gurudev Sri Sri Ravi Shankar, who explained, “meditation is the skill to calm the mind and connect with inner joy and peace, a state of deep rest and alertness. Meditation is the delicate art of doing nothing and letting go of all the efforts to relax into your true nature”; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_0AA1A8D7-886C-43F7-839E-0B008FC8BC3A"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, In 2024, the United Nations General Assembly proclaimed December 21 as World Meditation Day, recalling the right of everyone to the enjoyment of the highest attainable standard of physical and mental health; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_D512E54E-8EA5-4DEB-889C-1595F1458F20"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Meditation is a timeless practice that promotes mental, emotional, and physical well-being, fostering inner peace, clarity, and resilience; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_A451BB92-DA27-4736-9B5B-4E990E2A68A8"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Meditation can help people come out of depression and aggression, and has been scientifically proven to reduce stress, improve focus, enhance emotional health, and contribute to overall quality of life; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_7D194A39-5223-4B0E-8B13-BD6D671BB512"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The practice of meditation transcends cultural, religious, and socioeconomic boundaries, uniting individuals across the globe in a shared pursuit of mindfulness and self-awareness; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_0C6CB280-89B6-4A59-870F-E11E814924E7"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, December 21, the winter solstice, symbolizes a time of reflection, renewal, and the return of light, making it a fitting day to celebrate the transformative power of meditation; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_52AB9B72-2D6D-403E-8FE5-707A9710098A"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, World Meditation Day encourages individuals, communities, and organizations to pause, reflect, and engage in meditation practices, fostering a more compassionate and harmonious world; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_A123F14E-9C48-4D0F-9CF5-59AE08707DEB"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The State of California recognizes the importance of mental health and wellness, and supports initiatives that promote holistic approaches to well-being for all its residents; now, therefore, be it</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_DEF61FE9-2D09-4D97-8F46-7959E075EEB4"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Assembly of the State of California, That the Assembly hereby recognizes December 21, 2025, and annually thereafter, as World Meditation Day, encouraging all Californians to participate in meditation practices, whether individually or collectively, to cultivate peace, mindfulness, and unity; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_4769EB73-3F46-4651-8928-A7143494A08F"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Assembly encourages schools, workplaces, community organizations, and local governments to observe World Meditation Day by offering opportunities for meditation, mindfulness programs, and educational initiatives that highlight the benefits of this practice; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_5BA47FA2-C1AD-4A48-A6BD-B838755E2B28"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Assembly calls upon the residents of the State of California to embrace the spirit of World Meditation Day, recognizing the power of meditation to transform lives, strengthen communities, and contribute to a more peaceful and compassionate world; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_B8F890EC-89E0-459A-B66D-FB3E3C0040BB"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Chief Clerk of the Assembly transmit copies of this resolution to the author for appropriate distribution. </div></span></span></div></body></html>
